Here is a multiple-choice question in JSON format.
{
    "question": "Review the following Python code snippet:\\n\\n```python\\ndef outer_function():\\n    outer_value = 'Hello!'\\n    \\ndef inner_function():\\n        outer_value = 'Goodbye!'\\n    \\n    inner_function()\\n    print(outer_value)\\n\\nouter_function()\\n```\\n\\nWhat is printed when you run outer_function()?",
    "choices": [
        {
            "choice": "'Hello!'",
            "correct": "true"
        },
        {
            "choice": "'Goodbye!'",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "The program throws a NameError.",
            "correct": "false"
        }
    ]
}

Are the distractors that are completely unique, or are they similar?
